1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
Lighting decisions are often made from a plan and fixture schedule,
before anyone can feel the room at night.

2
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:25,000
This sample project opens directly in the 2D editor.
I select a light, adjust brightness, and choose a warmer color temperature.

3
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:37,000
The fast Edit view keeps adjustments responsive.
Realistic mode progressively path traces the same scene on supported hardware.

4
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Save a comparison and export a watermarked PNG.
Projects autosave locally and can also be exported as JSON.

5
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:59,000
The interface switches between Japanese and English.
On a phone, 2D, 3D, settings, and editing remain compact and accessible.

6
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:12,000
For this Build Week release, Codex with GPT-5.6 supported inspection,
bilingual implementation, feedback hardening, documentation, and validation.

7
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:20,200
LDK Lighting Lab helps people compare a home's nighttime atmosphere
before construction makes changes expensive.
